href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Languages/Congruences/RightCongruence.html#Cslib.RightCongruence.eqvCls\">RightCongruence.eqvCls</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The language of `c.toDA` with a single accepting state `s` is exactly\nthe equivalence class corresponding to `s`. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.html#Cslib.Automata.DA.FinAcc.congr_language_eq","kind":"theorem","line":56,"name":"Cslib.Automata.DA.FinAcc.congr_language_eq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.lean#L56-L61"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.html#Cslib.Automata.DA.congr_mtr_eq\"><span class=\"name\">Cslib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Automata</span>.<span class=\"name\">DA</span>.<span class=\"name\">congr_mtr_eq</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Languages/Congruences/RightCongruence.html#Cslib.RightCongruence\">RightCongruence</a> <span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">xs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.html#Cslib.RightCongruence.toDA\">RightCongruence.toDA</a>.<a href=\"./Cslib/Foundations/Semantics/FLTS/Basic.html#Cslib.FLTS.mtr\">mtr</a></span> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.html#Cslib.RightCongruence.toDA\">RightCongruence.toDA</a>.<a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Basic.html#Cslib.Automata.DA.start\">start</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">xs</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Quotient.mk\">⟦</a><span class=\"fn\">xs</span><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Quotient.mk\">⟧</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"After consuming a finite word `xs`, `c.toDA` reaches the state `⟦ xs ⟧` which is\nthe equivalence class of `xs`. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.html#Cslib.Automata.DA.congr_mtr_eq","kind":"theorem","line":39,"name":"Cslib.Automata.DA.congr_mtr_eq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.lean#L39-L50"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.html#Cslib.RightCongruence.toDA\"><span class=\"name\">Cslib</span>.<span class=\"name\">RightCongruence</span>.<span class=\"name\">toDA</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Languages/Congruences/RightCongruence.html#Cslib.RightCongruence\">RightCongruence</a> <span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Basic.html#Cslib.Automata.DA\">Automata.DA</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Quotient\">Quotient</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">c</span>.<a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Languages/Congruences/RightCongruence.html#Cslib.RightCongruence.eq\">eq</a></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Every right congruence gives rise to a DA whose states are the equivalence classes of\nthe right congruence, whose start state is the empty word, and whose transition functiuon\nis concatenation on the right of the input symbol. Note that the transition function is\nwell-defined only because `c` is a right congruence. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.html#Cslib.RightCongruence.toDA","kind":"def","line":22,"name":"Cslib.RightCongruence.toDA","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/b00648a4fe741981bb586a3cc845258ab1583f61/Cslib/Computability/Automata/DA/Congr.lean#L22-L33"}}],"imports":["Init","Cslib.Computability.Automata.DA.Basic","Cslib.Computability.Languages.Congruences.RightCongruence"],"instances":[],"name":"Cslib.Computability.Automata.DA.Congr"}